adamiano001 01-12-26 06:29:36: So you are getting a new Trophon and AuditPro handset, is that correct?
I would assume you will need both of those devices connected to the network. If they're both on the wireless network that would be the easiest then the AuditPro and Trophon can communicate with each other without firewall rules.
Will the Trophon and Audit Pro also need rules to communicate outside of our network? If yes I will need the vendor to provide a whitelisting document for all of the external destinations that are needed.
I apologize for being picky on this one but the last Trophon install we did at SMMC-LB (ID 1974 SMMC-LB Nanosonics Trophon2) had a lot of issues with connectivity and there was quite a bit of back and forth with the vendor for what was needed.
I'm happy to help get both devices connected if that's what we need but I'll need the wireless MAC addresses for both the Trophon and the AuditPro handset and a whitelisting document from the vendor.
CCing the Vendor here or starting a new thread may be helpful.
Thank you for your assistance.

