adamiano001 11-24-25 14:36:42: Nadia provided response from the vendor. Asked Dhaval to confirm if this device will be using a serial connection and if yes what those details are.
We DO NOT connect either of the LAN NICs to the facility interface (e.g. Cerner):
LAN 1 is the one we use to connect to the customers general network for use with LP Connect or Bruker.
LAN 2 is for our closed network.
If your configuration requires LP Connect or a Bruker connection then you would use LAN 1:
i.      Please identify the LAN 1 MAC and use that. We use a 10’s network on LAN 2 for our IP (e.g. 10.0.0.1). If the facility will use a 10’s IP scheme we will have to change ours. LAN 2 has 10.0.0.1 set and will update if required.
For the LIS Connection (This is the scenario for this configuration):
We use an available Serial COM port from our computer for an LIS connection. We do not use the TCPIP connection through either LAN 1 or LAN 2.
The Serial COM port will require CERNER to provide an RJ45 to DB9 adapter pined our in Serial Null Modem. That connects to a terminal server box and Likely iBUS.

