adamiano001 02-06-25 15:26:39: Per Jose Sanchez: During a recent meeting with Joe and the PACS team, it was brought to our attention that the bkSpecto device should not be sending images to our Radiology PACS. The reason for this is that there's an existing solution for the Gastroenterology department which is managed by the ClinApps Surgery team. The software solution is provided by Olympus and it's called VaultStream Easy Suite. The solution has their own VNA for image storage and other handy features which are outside my scope of knowledge at this time.
What this means is that there's a possibility that an MDICI might be needed to ask the ClinApps Surgery team to assess the onboarding of the bkSpecto currently residing in the GI Lab area. Wanted to make you aware of this before we continue down the path we thought would work prior to these news being known to us.

