Anthony Damiano <adamiano001>, 9/26/2024 6:52:14 AM:  Good Morning - is there any more information on if this project will continue through MDICI or if it's going to be installed through a different project?
Response from Bree: HI Anthony,
I have not heard anything further regarding this project from Randy or that Phil was able to get MAC info from the CD burner.  I do know that this burner will need to connect to a server, so it will ultimately need firewall rules and IP info assigned, but I think without the server info first, we can't progress any further.  I'll reach back out to Randy, but unless Phil has further information than I do, I would say we are at a pause until we have that server info.
Phil or Randy,
if you have further information on the status of the CD burner and/or server, please let us know.
___________________________________________________________
Anthony Damiano <adamiano001>, 9/12/2024 7:00:07 AM:  Team - is there any update on getting the MAC address for this MDICI effort? Do you still want to move forward with this install? RESPONSE from Bree:  My understanding is that Phil was going to attempt to get the MAC address for the CD burner with the help of a laptop.  That being said, the other part to and maybe required piece to this is that there is a ""workstation"" or ""server"" that we have requested from Randy and the IT project team, as the burner is engaged by this workstation and would need to be the piece of equipment that had firewall rules in place and connected singularly to the burner.
I've requested the project # from Randy so I can see if this could be handled by the Medical Imaging team.  I would say until we get the workstation/server in place, firewall rules may be not yet needed.
