ase let me know how many internal IP addresses and NATs will be needed for this system as soon as you can. I need this information before Monday or the Design Engineering team won't be able to start. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 7/23/2024 2:41:49 PM: Hello William - Your MDICI request has been received and assigned the following project number: ID 2297 SEQ Philips Azurion R2.2 This project is starting on: 7/29/24 Below are the connections requested for the device, please let me know if this isn't correct: If the device will be serviced remotely, can it be done using one of the following access methods: B2B VPN What is your PACS/CPACS vendor? Merge Cardio PACS What is the PACS Modality Worklist AE Title, IP address, and port this device will query for MWL? ""MWL AETITLE: BASA_RPACS_MWL MWL IP Address: 10.106.200.72 Port: 12200"" What is the PACS AE Title, IP address, and port which will receive images from this device? ""PACS AETitle: SEQ_FIC_CPACS PACS IP Address: 10.106.200.72 Port: 12008"" I'm adding Marla Stinson and Daniel Livy from Philips to this thread. Marla or Daniel - I understand the Azurion system being installed at Sequoia hospital will need two internal and two NAT IP addresses for the Azurion Host PC and Interventional Workstation, is that correct? I imagine the device will connect as shown in the diagram below. Please let me know if anything belows needs to be changed: This device will be going on VLAN: 713, please make sure you put in a network request to get ports configured for this VLAN if you don't already have them. From the start date of the project it can take up to four weeks before the device is ready to test. I have marked this as a ""High"" priority request so hopefully we get IPs and firewall rules in place a lot sooner than that. Once this project is ready to test I will send out networking information with the technical design in a separate email. Let me know if you have any questions. _