Jimmy Wu,2270,,Enterprise,MMCR,Complete,Lab,2024-06-17,ID 2270 (2250) MMCR Sysmex DI-60,1,Security Review add'l entry for Sam.,Sara Teuscher /  Jeanette McBroome,"Anthony Damiano , 6/24/2024 10:00:25 AM: Firewall - SCTASK6375373 - ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/20/2024 2:04:49 PM: Modality onboarding: REQ4570323 ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/10/2024 4:01:40 PM: MACs received. Waiting on IP address of Kyocera printer they want to add to the design. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/6/2024 11:07:32 AM: Emailed the site to clarify which units will need to have IP addresses assigned. See email below. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/6/2024 11:07:26 AM: Hello Jeanette - Your MDICI request has been received and assigned the following project number: ID 2250 MMCR Sysmex XN-3100 I have some questions about the intake that was submitted that I need clarification on. You submitted three MDS2 documents, Cellavision DM, SP-50 and XN Series. Will all three of these devices need network connectivity? I understand the XN3100 and Cellavision will connect to your term servers but will they all need a separate TCP/IP connection to connect to Sysmex for remote support? What system(s) will this device be connected to? Term Server - Ports 11 and 13. 11 for Sysmex XN3100 and 13 for Cellavision I've included Zackery Sommer from Sysmex on this thread. I will need the MAC addresses of the units needing connectivity for remote support so we can assign IPs and firewall rules. Device MAC address(es): PENDING - Per Salil, okay to submit form without the mac address If the device will be serviced remotely, can it be done using one of the following access methods: Port 443 TLS Communications I'm also including the lab team, Dhaval, Dusty and Andrea on this thread. I imagine the connectivity diagram will look similar to this: MDICI Above 2100 - 2250.jpeg Please verify which units will need to have IPs assigned to them and provide the MAC addresses when you can. As soon as I understand the connectivity requirements for the devices I will assign resources and a start date. From the start date of the project it can take up to four weeks before the device is ready to test. Once this project is ready to test I will send out networking information with the technical design in a separate email. Let me know if you have any questions. Thank you, ___________________________________________________________",2024-06-20,2024-06-20,,Northern California,653.0,2024-07-05,Completed,,3.0,3.0,,2026-04-01 21:30:08.188085,CORLCYB001
