Kyle Johnston,2251,,Central California,BMH,Complete,Imaging-RAD,2024-06-10,ID 2251 BMH GE Allia IGS 7,1,Testing complete per Susanne LaFond.,Phi Tran / Phil Moriarty / Ed Trogdon,"Anthony Damiano , 8/15/2024 2:27:26 PM: Asked Walt Wolf to check the firewall rules to GE InSite URLs, they look to be blocked on the site firewall. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 8/7/2024 11:40:40 AM: Testing complete per Susanne LaFond. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 7/29/2024 9:05:40 AM: 08/01/2024 @0700 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/21/2024 10:00:48 AM: Testing info sent to site. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/17/2024 10:58:04 AM: Firewall - SCTASK6328885 - Walt Wolf ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/14/2024 11:28:55 AM: Modality onboarding: REQ4549114 ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/6/2024 3:38:30 PM: Hello Phil - Your MDICI request has been received and assigned the following project number: ID 2251 BMH GE Allia IGS Below are the connections requested for the device. If this needs to change please let me know: What is your PACS/CPACS vendor? Merge What is the PACS Modality Worklist AE Title, IP address, and port this device will query for MWL?AETitle: MWL, IP Address: 10.177.200.41, Port: 12200 What is the PACS AE Title, IP address, and port which will receive images from this device? AETitle: BMH_CARD, IP Address: 10.177.200.41, Port: 12009 It was also requested that the unit be put on the GE B2B VPN but the last GE Allia installed at BMH (ID 2074 BMH GE Allia IGS, February, 2024, design attached) was connected to GE InSite over port 443. I'm adding Dean and Tim from GE to verify which connection is preferred for this unit. Phil - you also mentioned wanting to use the old IP from cath lab 2: Additional comments: Intention is to reuse the previous IP address that was Cath Lab 2 The standard is to put all new imaging devices on VLAN 713. Please make sure to put in a request to get a port configured for VLAN 713. Once you provide the MAC address I will assign resources and a start date. From the start date of the project it can take up to four weeks before the device is ready to test. Once this project is ready to test I will send out networking information with the technical design in a separate email. Let me know if you have any questions. ___________________________________________________________",2024-06-21,2024-06-14,2024-08-07,Southern California,660.0,2024-06-28,Completed,,11.0,4.0,58.0,2026-04-01 21:30:08.188085,CORLCYB001
