Nancy Kupihea,1839,,Greater Sacramento,MSJMC,Complete,Imaging-RAD,2023-06-05,ID 1839 MSJMC Optos Monaco P200TE,1,Project Closed.,Frank Lindeman / Peter Kulak / Christopher Nauta / Tom Miller,"Anthony Damiano , 10/24/2023 6:44:07 AM: Project closed after no response to project being in testing for over 90 days. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 10/12/2023 7:46:51 AM: Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 10/2/2023 11:04:23 AM: Let site know testing information was sent out for this project over 90 days ago. This project will be closed at the end of the week if we don't receive a response. RESPONSE from Peter Kulak: Testing can not be completed until the Optos quote for DICOM capabilities to be enabled has been paid by Dr. Martel. Dr. Martel has agreed to pay for the DICOM capability to be enabled. Once the vendor has received payment, they will enable it and we can start connectivity testing to/from PACS. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 9/20/2023 7:48:33 AM: 09/21/2023 @ 0700 - Asked site for testing update. RESPONSE from Peter Kulak: We're not able to do any testing on #1839 until a DICOM package is purchased for the device from the vendor. Dr. Lanam is working with Dr. Martel on the purchase. Once the vendor has the PO, We can start configuration and testing. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 8/31/2023 6:50:52 AM: Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 8/9/2023 7:20:18 AM: 08/10/2023 @ 0700 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 8/2/2023 8:35:32 AM: From Chris Nauta: ""Here's where we are with the OPTOS currently: The new PC that was installed recently has already been physically damaged (photo), and further testing is not possible at this time. Why? - The PC outputs video in either DisplayPort or HDMI formats only. It appears the only DP port on the video card/MOBO is destroyed. I've ordered an HDMI-> DP adapter to try that port as a workaround. Still waiting on that adapter to come in. The display only accepts VGA or DP, so I can't go HDMI straight into the monitor. I'm optimistic that the HDMI port will get us going without needing a major PC repair/replacement etc, and will let you know as soon as the part comes in and I can check it out."" ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 8/2/2023 8:09:34 AM: Response from Peter Kulak - "":Hi Anthony, Last week I forwarded the IP information for the MSJMC Optos Monaco P200TE (ID 1839) and met with Chris Nauta (Clinical Engineering). I showed him where the device is located in the ED. He's going to work with the vendor and configure the device. He's going to let me know as soon as it's ready for testing modality worklist and sending images to PACS."" ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 7/18/2023 7:06:38 AM: 07/20/2023 @0700 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/28/2023 10:34:08 AM: Testing info sent to site. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/27/2023 9:13:33 AM: Firewall: SCTASK4505556 - John Patty ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 6/23/2023 11:51:15 AM: Modality onboarding: REQ3203273 ___________________________________________________________",2023-06-28,2023-06-23,2023-10-24,Northern California,1031.0,2023-06-23,Completed,,23.0,18.0,141.0,2026-04-01 21:30:08.188085,CORLCYB001
