Christopher Harrow,1730,,Greater Sacramento,SNMH,Complete,Imaging-RAD,2023-03-14,ID 1730 SNMH Carestream DRX Evolution,1,Testing complete per Mark Little.,Mark Little,"Anthony Damiano , 6/8/2023 7:35:38 AM: Testing complete per Mark Little. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 6/7/2023 10:12:19 AM: 06/08/2023 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 5/16/2023 8:30:31 PM: 5/18/23 - Asked site for testing update. RESPONSE form Mark Little: Still prepping room. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 4/24/2023 8:35:12 AM: 4/27/23 - Asked site for testing updates. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 4/5/2023 8:12:15 AM: 4/6/23 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/16/2023 8:08:57 AM: Testing info sent to site. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/14/2023 1:23:47 PM: Modality onboarding: REQ2815963. Firewall: SCTASK3988070 (Bill Maurer) ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 2/9/2023 12:15:25 PM: Per Charles Restivo with Carestream (see attached ""Smart Link Customer Site Firewall Configuration_AH4213.pdf"") For RMS, we need to communicate to the Production Server and a GAS ( Global Access Server ) The Production Server is used for Monitoring and the GAS Server is used for Remote Desktop Presently, the US uses the one in Somerville ( 209.202.157.179 ) We do suggest that we have access to all of the GAS servers in case the one goes down ( It has happened ) and then we get redirected to another server. I would suggest that we have all of the GAS servers that are highlighted in Bold lettering Port 443 we use to get an outbound connection. When we want to remote in, we send a request that the next time the device is contacted ( part of Remote Monitoring ) that we leave the tunnel open, so we then can remote in. Port 53 is used for DNS ( Only for Imageview Software ) We do not use a HOSTS file anymore to resolve the Host name / IP Address for the Production Server Our older Directview software would use either DNS of HOST File ___________________________________________________________",2023-03-16,2023-03-14,2023-06-08,Northern California,1114.0,2023-03-31,Completed,,2.0,0.0,86.0,2026-04-01 21:30:08.188085,CORLCYB001
