Chris Coleman,1678,,Greater Sacramento,SNMH,Complete,Imaging-RAD,2023-02-13,ID 1678 SNMH Carestream DRX Evolution,1,Testing complete per Mark Little.,Mark Little,"Anthony Damiano , 4/6/2023 11:39:17 AM: Testing complete per Mark Little. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 4/5/2023 8:12:11 AM: 4/6/23 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Bulk Comment Update 3/14/2023 8:03:49 AM: 03/16/23 - Asked site for testing update. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/14/2023 9:48:06 AM: Additional firewall rule requested under SCTASK3978270. Implemented and let site know it's ready to test. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/2/2023 9:48:06 AM: Testing info sent to site. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/2/2023 9:29:43 AM: Asked DE to update TD so I can send out testing info. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 3/1/2023 9:39:18 AM: Modality onobarding: REQ2756254 ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 2/9/2023 12:15:25 PM: Per Charles Restivo with Carestream (see attached ""Smart Link Customer Site Firewall Configuration_AH4213.pdf"") For RMS, we need to communicate to the Production Server and a GAS ( Global Access Server ) The Production Server is used for Monitoring and the GAS Server is used for Remote Desktop Presently, the US uses the one in Somerville ( 209.202.157.179 ) We do suggest that we have access to all of the GAS servers in case the one goes down ( It has happened ) and then we get redirected to another server. I would suggest that we have all of the GAS servers that are highlighted in Bold lettering Port 443 we use to get an outbound connection. When we want to remote in, we send a request that the next time the device is contacted ( part of Remote Monitoring ) that we leave the tunnel open, so we then can remote in. Port 53 is used for DNS ( Only for Imageview Software ) We do not use a HOSTS file anymore to resolve the Host name / IP Address for the Production Server Our older Directview software would use either DNS of HOST File ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 2/9/2023 12:06:02 PM: We will move forward with this project and the internal connections listed in the ""description"" section (and intake spreadsheet) and will add the remote support connections once Carestream verified URLs/IPs and ports. ___________________________________________________________ Anthony Damiano , 2/6/2023 8:17:05 PM: Waiting for site to confirm if this device needs remote support or not before assigning a start date and resources. ___________________________________________________________",2023-03-02,2023-03-01,2023-04-06,Northern California,1143.0,2023-03-03,Completed,,17.0,16.0,52.0,2026-04-01 21:30:08.188085,CORLCYB001
