Lenczewski, Michael - PHX , 5/10/2021 3:21:44 PM:  Per the vendor: Remote Access Solution - Compliance Questions
1) Does the vendor have a contract (BAA if PHI present) with CommonSpirit Health? @Jaber, Majid do you know where we are at with this?
2) Can remote support access/actions be logged with a unique identifier, date and time and relevant source/destination for data transmissions? Medtronic support personnel have unique login. All access and activity is logged. From the customer side, this will utilize the authentication method of the device. The Customer must accept and choose our level of access when initiating a session.
3) Does CommonSpirit Health have an identified business or technical owner that can produce on demand on premise logs or for hosted systems document how to obtain copies of logs, log reports, and/or review reports? Logs are available upon request, your local Medtronic Rep will be the point of contact.
4) Does all traffic use end-to-end data encryption where there is no intermediate decryption of the transmission by the third-party tool provider if the traffic traverses a public network? Yes
5) Does the remote access require a unique username/password or the ability to log all accesses to a unique vendor username? Yes
6) For shared desktop sessions can CommonSpirit Health manually initiate /accept to allow remote access? Yes, session must be initiated by Common Spirit
7) Does the solution encrypt all data, including passwords end to end, when it is transmitted across the internet (does not use FTP, Telnet, SMTP, HTTP, POP3, SQL, NETB, etc.)? Yes
8) Is sensitive data encrypted in transmission outside of CommonSpirit Health's network using secure protocols such as SFTP or HTTPS (TLS 1.2 or later)? Yes, data is encrypted with TLS 1.2
